{"questionId":"87a75825-ef1b-4b13-8fde-816390546062_4","correctAnswer":"C","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Set up","content":"Plug $x = 8$ into $g(x) = 7x^{-1}$: $$g(8) = 7(8)^{-1} = \\frac{7}{8}$$"},{"title":"Solve","content":"A negative exponent means reciprocal: $7 \\cdot \\frac{1}{8} = \\frac{7}{8}$."},{"title":"Answer","content":"<strong>C</strong> is correct."}]}